en_398191_0	Colonel Chaminda Wijayarathna of the Sri Lanka Light Infantry (SLLI) assumed office as the Commander, 622 Infantry Brigade under the Security Force Headquarters - Wanni on Monday (2) during a simple ceremony at the Brigade Headquarters in Welioya.
en_398191_1	Upon his reach there, the newly-appointed Brigade Commander was greeted to a Guard Turn Out at the main entrance of the Brigade Headquarters before he was conducted to the office.
en_398191_2	Amidst religious blessings, he left his signature for an official document to signify the acceptance of the new appointment, flanked by Commanding Officers of 9 Gajaba Regiment (GR), 20 GR and staff in the Brigade.
en_398191_3	Later, he planted a sapling in the premises as a symbol of memory before he addressed the troops.
en_398191_4	An all rank tea arrangement culminated the dayâ€™s proceedings.
